---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Support the Event"
  description="Learn about the volunteer-driven nature of DnD Day and how registration costs help make the event possible."
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <p class="section-title">Community Driven</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-4">
        <span class="gold-gradient">Support the Event</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        DnD Day is made possible by passionate volunteers and community support.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Message -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="card bg-dnd-primary/5 border-dnd-primary">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
            <span class="text-4xl">&#x2764;</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-dnd-primary">
              A Labor of Love
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-dnd-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
            DnD Day is a <strong class="text-dnd-primary"
              >not-for-profit event</strong
            > organized entirely by volunteers. We're a group of passionate D&D enthusiasts
            who believe in creating memorable experiences for our community.
          </p>
          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Every aspect of this event&mdash;from crafting the campaign story
            and designing encounters, to building terrain and coordinating
            logistics&mdash;is done by people freely giving their time because
            they love this hobby and want to share it with others.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Contribute -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
          <p class="section-title">Volunteer Contributions</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display">
            <span class="gold-gradient">What Goes Into DnD Day</span>
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="card">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-4 block">&#x1F4DC;</span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-2">
              Story & Campaign Design
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Writing the narrative, designing encounters, balancing combat, and
              ensuring all four theaters interconnect seamlessly.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-4 block">&#x1F3B2;</span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-2">
              Dungeon Mastering
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Our DMs volunteer their time to prepare, practice, and run
              engaging sessions for each theater of war.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-4 block">&#x1F3D4;</span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-2">Terrain & Props</h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Handcrafted battle maps, 3D terrain pieces, miniatures, and
              atmospheric props to bring the invasion to life.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-4 block">&#x1F4CB;</span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-dnd-primary mb-2">
              Event Coordination
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              Managing registrations, coordinating schedules, handling
              logistics, and making sure everything runs smoothly.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Registration Cost -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
          <p class="section-title">Registration</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display">
            <span class="gold-gradient">Event Costs</span>
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
            <span class="text-4xl">&#x1F4B0;</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-dnd-text">
              Why There's a Registration Fee
            </h3>
          </div>

          <p class="text-dnd-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
            While our time and effort are freely given, there are some hard
            costs we simply cannot absorb. The most significant is <strong
              class="text-dnd-primary">venue booking</strong
            >&mdash;securing a space large enough to host multiple tables
            simultaneously requires a rental fee.
          </p>

          <p class="text-dnd-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
            To cover these essential expenses, there will likely be a small
            registration cost to participate. We don't yet know the exact
            amount, but our commitment is clear:
          </p>

          <div class="bg-dnd-bg rounded-lg p-6 border border-dnd-border">
            <p class="text-center text-lg font-display text-dnd-primary mb-2">
              Maximum Value, Minimum Cost
            </p>
            <p class="text-center text-dnd-text-muted text-sm">
              We aim to provide the best possible experience for the lowest
              possible price. Every dollar of registration goes directly toward
              making the event happen&mdash;nothing more.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mt-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">&#x2753;</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-display text-dnd-text">
              What Does the Fee Cover?
            </h3>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-dnd-text-muted">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-dnd-primary">&#x2713;</span>
              <span>Venue rental and booking fees</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-dnd-primary">&#x2713;</span>
              <span>Basic supplies and materials</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-dnd-primary">&#x2713;</span>
              <span>Any other unavoidable event expenses</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Help -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dnd-bg-secondary">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="section-title">Get Involved</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display mb-6">
          <span class="gold-gradient">Want to Help?</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-dnd-text-muted mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
          If you're interested in volunteering, contributing terrain or props,
          or helping out in any other way, we'd love to hear from you!
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact the Organizers</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display mb-4">
        <span class="gold-gradient">Ready to Join the Fight?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-dnd-text-muted mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Sign up to be notified when registration opens for Operation Golden
        Sword.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-primary">Sign Up Now</a>
        <a href="/crew" class="btn btn-secondary">Meet the Crew</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
